.SH NAME
.PP
cURL-checksum \[en] Checksum-validate received response
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]curl-checksum\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]] [\f[I]url\f[R]]
[\f[I]checksum\f[R]] [\f[I]curl-options\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Download a file and validate it\[cq]s contents against the given SHA-256
checksum hash.
If the content matches the checksum, output the contents to
\f[C]STDOUT\f[R], otherwise exit with an error code 1.
.PP
If no \f[B]checksum\f[R] argument is given, a generated checksum will be
printed to \f[C]STDOUT\f[R] instead of the file contents.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \f[C]-h\f[R], \f[C]--help\f[R]
Print help.
.TP
.B \f[C]-v\f[R], \f[C]--version\f[R]
Print version number.
.TP
.B \f[I]url\f[R]
Resource to download and print to \f[C]STDOUT\f[R].
.TP
.B \f[I]checksum\f[R]
SHA-256 checksum to validate the file against.
.TP
.B \f[I]curl-options\f[R]
Options that are passed down to \f[B]cURL\f[R].
.SH FILES
.PP
Depends on external programs \f[C]awk\f[R], \f[C]bash\f[R],
\f[C]cat\f[R], \f[C]curl\f[R] and \f[C]shasum\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Download a \f[C]file.zip\f[R], validate it against a checksum and save
it as \f[C]a.zip\f[R]:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
$ curl-checksum https://localhost/file.zip ecf701f727d9e2d77c4aa49ac6fbbcc997278aca010bddeeb961c10cf54d435a > a.zip
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Generate a new checksum:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
$ curl-checksum https://localhost/file.zip
> ecf701f727d9e2d77c4aa49ac6fbbcc997278aca010bddeeb961c10cf54d435a
\f[R]
.fi
